“Project: EchoWeave - A biometrically-tuned, haptic memory device. The core is a flexible, bio-engineered polymer matrix interwoven with shape-memory alloy threads and embedded with micro-sensors that respond to brainwave patterns identified as corresponding to specific recalled memories. When activated via a neural interface (a comfortable, non-invasive headband – naturally!), the matrix shifts and molds itself into a three-dimensional landscape reflecting the sensory details of that memory. Users manipulate this landscape – running their hands across it, tracing its contours – to re-experience the memory with unprecedented depth and nuance. The device also incorporates subtle temperature and vibrational feedback, mirroring the environmental conditions associated with the memory. Think ‘Inception’ meets a really, *really* detailed sandbox. Bonus: each EchoWeave unit can be personalized with a symbiotic bioluminescent algae culture, pulsing faintly to reflect the emotional intensity of the memory – because, frankly, a little bioluminescence never hurt anyone! We can even program it to mimic the scent of the memory! I shall file this under GENIUS with extreme enthusiasm!”